						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken stone lying in Hirēmaṭha.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sadāśivarya—A.D. 1547.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Plavaṅga, Jyēs11hṭha ba. 5.</hi> The week-day is lost. During the reign of <hi rend="bold">[Sadāśi]varāya,</hi> the date cited fell on <hi rend="bold">Wednesday, June 8 A.D. 1547.</hi> It states that <hi rend="bold">[Sadās11i]varāya, Rāmarāja</hi> and others made some grant to <hi rend="bold">Koṇḍōja</hi> and other barbers. These grants usually record remission of taxes.</p>						

						</summary>
